Ask HN: Has the ChatGPT spam tidal wave already begun?
text:
LinkedIn was never exactly the font of great writing, but recently I've started to see posts that have some of the weird hallmarks of GPT output (restating the same not terribly interesting points for multiple paragraphs in a row for example) showing up in my LinkedIn feed. I'm a bit afraid to ask the posters if they used the bot to write their posts, but I'm curious to see if anyone else is seeing the same. I had figured phishing was going to be the first venue. Or is this just AI induced paranoia?

(Links omitted to protect the guilty)

Ask HN: How do you plan on making money with Open AI API?
text:
It seems that compared to DaVinci, the other 3 models are pretty difficult to effectively use. I spent hours trying to get usable results with Curie, but to no avail.

I'm just curious to know from those who are building applications using Open AI APIs, how are you planning on monetizing your applications when it costs 1-2 cents to get a decent result. That is quite expensive.
